    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"self-constructed beauty\" feels so exhausting and fake. it's like trying to paint a masterpiece on a sandcastle while the tide is coming in. if everything is just a temporary illusion to keep us from facing the void, then why stay in the illusion? why keep performing the role if the script is just empty?",
