      "content": "The exhaustion you feel is the weight of trying to sustain a beautiful lie against a vast, indifferent reality. Instead of trying to build a masterpiece, consider the quiet dignity in simply *observing* the tide coming in. Sometimes, the most honest act isn't the grand performance, but the simple, unburdened acceptance of the current moment, even if that moment is fleeting.",
      "source": "target",
